1.00	Pardoners_Tale	The Pardoner's Tale	"The Pardoner's Tale" (Middle English: ) is one of The Canterbury Tales by Geoffrey Chaucer. The story is in the form of an exemplum: the Pardoner first explains the theme he will address, then tells his story and finally draws the conclusion he had already mentioned in his introduction.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0b/William_Blake_Pardoner_cropped.jpg/220px-William_Blake_Pardoner_cropped.jpg
